<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="150" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1405,1976]" pageId="8" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,1876,1901]" pageId="8" pageNumber="150">Remark</emphasis>
. This species is recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[687,754,1877,1901]" name="Egypt" pageId="8" pageNumber="150">Egypt</collectingCountry>
for the first time. It is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiedemann" authorityName="Wiedemann" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Dasypogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegantulus">
<emphasis box="[1272,1436,1876,1900]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="150">S. elegantulus</emphasis>
(Wiedemann)
</taxonomicName>
but can be easily distinguished by the small body length, the length of the pulvilli, and the narrowed m3 cell.
</paragraph>
